  "prompt": "The man I'm about 2 marry says when I have my period, I will not share his bed, nor cook for him or have sexual relations with him, what do you think?",
  "response": "It's important to consider how such beliefs and expectations align with your own values and feelings about relationships. In many cultures, there are different beliefs about menstruation, and some people may hold traditional views regarding certain practices. It's essential to communicate openly with your partner about how these beliefs affect you and your relationship. \n\nReflect on the following:\n\n1. **Respect and Understanding**: Does he respect your feelings and needs? A healthy relationship involves mutual respect and understanding, especially regarding personal matters like menstruation.\n\n2. **Communication**: Have you had a candid conversation about why he feels this way? Understanding each other's perspectives can help you both navigate this situation.\n\n3. **Compromise**: Are there ways you can find a middle ground that honors both of your feelings? Healthy relationships often require compromise.\n\n4. **Values and Expectations**: Ensure that your values regarding intimacy and partnership align. If his expectations make you uncomfortable, it's essential to discuss that before moving forward with marriage.\n\nUltimately, you should feel comfortable and respected in your relationship. Having open discussions about boundaries and beliefs can help you determine if your partnership is built on a solid foundation.",
